01:00.825 --> 01:01.562
Jordan.

01:16.186 --> 01:18.416
You don't have to keep vigil, shawn.

01:18.553 --> 01:20.819
Are you going to cancel the appearance at riverfront park?

01:20.820 --> 01:22.263
No. That would be a mistake.

01:22.264 --> 01:23.617
They're not just honoring me.

01:24.103 --> 01:26.676
They're honoring the center and all the work we've done.

01:28.304 --> 01:31.738
- A new neurological clinic just opened in atlanta.
- No, look, look.

01:31.766 --> 01:34.908
I've been to all the specialists, shawn.

01:35.073 --> 01:36.646
There's no name for what I have.

01:36.880 --> 01:38.141
We can't just give up.

01:38.252 --> 01:40.668
There's got to be a way to
figure out what that baby did to you.

01:40.670 --> 01:42.222
I know what that baby did to me.

01:42.223 --> 01:43.344
It saved my life.

01:44.429 --> 01:44.940
What?

01:45.175 --> 01:46.107
What are you talking about?

01:46.382 --> 01:49.633
When I touched lily's pregnant
belly and was hit with that pain

01:49.634 --> 01:52.363
I realized I'd been judged and found wanting.

01:52.364 --> 01:55.743
- By a baby that wasn't even born yet?
- In that moment...

01:58.010 --> 02:00.501
I was forced to see the truth about myself,

02:00.527 --> 02:03.104
about my motives toward the 4400,

02:03.832 --> 02:05.897
and they were... not pure.

02:05.972 --> 02:07.626
That baby tried to kill you.

02:08.062 --> 02:09.282
And it succeeded.

02:10.262 --> 02:12.086
It killed the old jordan collier,

02:12.299 --> 02:15.632
and I was reborn,

02:16.619 --> 02:17.888
pure of purpose.

02:18.982 --> 02:20.322
All I've done since,

02:20.399 --> 02:21.525
everything I've built,

02:21.528 --> 02:22.819
I owe to richard,

02:23.524 --> 02:27.602
to lily... and to that child.

02:32.047 --> 02:32.895
I'll get it.

02:40.345 --> 02:41.766
- Hey.
- Hi.

02:42.681 --> 02:44.184
Come in. Lily...

02:44.993 --> 02:45.916
Iook who's here.

02:48.168 --> 02:49.277
We would have called,

02:49.278 --> 02:51.055
but heidi wanted to surprise you.

02:52.478 --> 02:53.242
Heidi...

02:53.645 --> 02:54.680
hi, mom.

02:55.844 --> 02:57.004
She's so cute.

02:57.008 --> 02:58.652
Now that you guys are living on the block,

02:58.916 --> 03:01.143
I figured it was time for heidi to meet her real mom.

03:01.764 --> 03:03.406
That makes you my second dad.

03:04.211 --> 03:05.054
I guess so.

03:05.847 --> 03:07.218
Mom, why are you crying?

03:07.219 --> 03:08.514
Lily, are you all right?

03:09.623 --> 03:10.512
- Lily?
- Lily?

03:12.699 --> 03:14.100
Lily?

03:16.201 --> 03:17.004
Lily?

03:18.053 --> 03:19.146
Sweetheart, wake up.

03:25.463 --> 03:26.425
It was a dream...

03:26.575 --> 03:27.899
more like a nightmare.

03:29.376 --> 03:30.561
No, no.

03:31.703 --> 03:33.510
We were living next door to heidi and brian,

03:34.155 --> 03:36.104
and we were all getting along.
And the house...

03:36.679 --> 03:38.158
richard, it was so pretty.

03:38.277 --> 03:39.413
So why were you crying?

03:42.417 --> 03:43.899
I guess I knew it wasn't real.

03:47.698 --> 03:50.493
How long can we keep going
before someone catches up to us?

03:51.700 --> 03:53.337
We just got to keep moving,

03:53.507 --> 03:55.438
stay ahead of collier and ntac.

03:57.304 --> 03:59.245
I'm just so tired of running.

03:59.533 --> 04:01.470
We're going to find a place to stop running.

04:02.381 --> 04:03.430
It's out there...

04:03.497 --> 04:04.647
got to be.

04:52.574 --> 04:54.394
That's good.

04:54.405 --> 04:55.416
You've come so far.

04:59.543 --> 05:01.031
Nice use of color.

05:07.272 --> 05:09.050
It's shaping up, greg,

05:09.281 --> 05:11.388
