18:04.700 --> 18:06.900
I need you to call the sheriff's office in weldon. Idaho.

18:07.000 --> 18:08.000
See what you can find out.

18:08.100 --> 18:09.300
Well. I don't know what I can do for the guy.

18:09.400 --> 18:11.500
I'm not a criminal lawyer.

18:11.700 --> 18:13.000
Brian. If you don't want to help...

18:13.100 --> 18:14.400
I swear to god. Lily.

18:14.500 --> 18:15.800
You disappear for over a year.

18:15.900 --> 18:18.900
And then you call me up with these stories 
about the police arresting your boyfriend...

18:18.901 --> 18:21.200
richard's my husband.

18:21.400 --> 18:23.100
We have a child.

18:23.200 --> 18:25.600
A six-month-old girl.

18:29.500 --> 18:31.300
How's heidi?

18:32.200 --> 18:33.700
She's good.

18:33.800 --> 18:36.400
Started seventh grade and...

18:36.500 --> 18:38.700
aced her first semester.

18:39.000 --> 18:40.800
That's wonderful.

18:42.500 --> 18:43.900
Brian.

18:44.000 --> 18:45.000
I'm sorry to be bothering you with this.

18:45.100 --> 18:48.600
But I have nowhere else to turn.

18:51.400 --> 18:54.700
Okay. I'll make a few calls and do whatever I can.

18:59.000 --> 18:59.900
I got to admit.

19:00.000 --> 19:03.300
The first time mike came home with 
that violin and started playing.

19:03.400 --> 19:05.600
His mom and me. We were both a little spooked.

19:05.700 --> 19:07.400
So why did you help pay heather's bail?

19:07.500 --> 19:10.000
I would've paid the whole thing if I could've afforded it.

19:10.100 --> 19:12.800
My wife. She shot a video of mike playing.

19:12.900 --> 19:14.700
Sent it over to the conservatory.

19:14.800 --> 19:16.400
Next day. They called back.

19:16.500 --> 19:18.800
Said our son was a prodigy.

19:18.900 --> 19:20.700
Did you tell them he'd been playing for only two weeks?

19:20.800 --> 19:22.600
Well. They thought I was putting them on.

19:22.700 --> 19:26.700
Talked about how his playing was worthy of a scholarship.

19:26.800 --> 19:31.100
You know. I thought this kid was going to wind 
up working on the assembly line like his old man.

19:31.200 --> 19:33.000
Now he's got a way out.

19:33.100 --> 19:34.100
Hmm.

19:34.300 --> 19:36.600
Ms. Tobey's at ntac today for a physical.

19:36.700 --> 19:39.500
We're asking the parents of the students she's 
"gifted" to come in to be interviewed.

19:39.600 --> 19:41.500
No problem. I'll call his mom.

19:41.600 --> 19:44.400
We'll do anything we need to to get 
heather back in that classroom.

19:44.500 --> 19:45.600
Great.

19:45.700 --> 19:46.500
Thanks.

19:46.600 --> 19:48.700
You should've seen them chowing down on the pizza.

19:48.800 --> 19:49.500
Just getting enough to eat.

19:49.600 --> 19:50.900
You konw it's such a struggle.

19:51.000 --> 19:53.600
And you made that struggle a little easier.

19:53.700 --> 19:54.500
I'm proud of you. Shawn.

19:54.600 --> 19:56.900
I'm thinking about going back down there.

19:57.000 --> 19:59.400
There's so much they need... jackets. Sleeping bags.

19:59.500 --> 20:02.500
Maybe a couple of first aid kits.

20:02.600 --> 20:04.700
Basic stuff to survive. You know.

20:04.800 --> 20:06.600
You give them all the supplies they need.

20:06.700 --> 20:07.900
- All right.
- But look.

20:08.000 --> 20:09.700
Whatever you do. Shawn.

20:09.800 --> 20:12.800
Don't reveal your healing ability.

20:13.000 --> 20:14.500
Why?

20:14.600 --> 20:17.000
'Cause they can't pay? No.

20:17.100 --> 20:18.700
Because if you heal one of them.

20:18.800 --> 20:21.000
You'll have to heal them all.

20:21.100 --> 20:22.600
I mean it.

20:23.100 --> 20:25.400
Not even you can do that.

20:29.800 --> 20:31.200
Yeah.

20:31.600 --> 20:33.200
I'm listening.

20:34.800 --> 20:36.500
When was this?

21:23.300 --> 21:24.100
Sweet.

21:24.200 --> 21:25.700
I'm a little rusty.

21:25.800 --> 21:28.300
One of these days. I'm going to write a concept album

21:28.400 --> 21:29.800
about my time on the street.

21:29.900 --> 21:30.600
Oh.

21:30.800 --> 21:32.900
I'm gonna win a grammy.

21:33.000 --> 21:34.600
Make the bling-bling.

21:34.700 --> 21:36.400
You know. And get a private jet.

21:36.500 --> 21:42.000
One of those big old gated houses with enough 
room for wayne. Kimmy. And shadow.

21:47.100 --> 21:49.200
Sounds like a plan.

21:50.400 --> 21:53.700
Yeah. It matches your eyes. Sweetie.

21:54.700 --> 21:56.100
Hey.

21:57.100 --> 21:59.400
First time in months I haven't seen him shivering.

21:59.500 --> 22:01.900
It's amazing what a warm coat'll do.

22:02.400 --> 22:04.700
You got yourself that guitar. Huh?

22:05.100 --> 22:07.000
No. Actually. You know what?

22:07.100 --> 22:09.000
I got you a guitar.

22:13.700 --> 22:15.200
What's the matter. Baby girl?

22:15.300 --> 22:17.900
You act like you never had a present before.

22:21.200 --> 22:23.000
It's been a while.

22:27.500 --> 22:29.700
You touch this. You die.

22:30.900 --> 22:32.700
- "Touch it. You die?"
- I guess so.

22:32.800 --> 22:34.600
What does that mean?

22:36.200 --> 22:38.100
I hate lines. Hate waiting in 'em.

22:38.200 --> 22:40.400
Trust me. There'll be no waiting tonight.

22:40.500 --> 22:41.300
I been to this club plenty of times.

22:41.400 --> 22:43.700
I know the bouncer. He'll let us walk right in.

22:43.800 --> 22:44.200
I hope you're right.

22:44.300 --> 22:46.700
I hate waiting in lines.

22:46.800 --> 22:49.800
Hey. That book you're reading is nothing but lies.

22:50.600 --> 22:51.700
Excuse me.

22:51.800 --> 22:53.200
I'm talking to you.

22:53.300 --> 22:55.400
That trash is going to rot your mind.

22:55.500 --> 22:57.400
Danny. What's going on?

22:57.500 --> 22:59.000
She ought to be careful.

22:59.100 --> 23:00.600
That book's a load of bull.

23:00.700 --> 23:01.900
- I bought it for her.
- Yeah?

23:02.000 --> 23:03.100
Big mistake.

23:03.200 --> 23:04.000
Anyone ask your opinion?

23:04.001 --> 23:05.400
Danny. Come on. Man.

23:05.500 --> 23:07.200
Just watch my back. Okay?

23:07.300 --> 23:08.200
Listen. Pal.

23:08.300 --> 23:11.000
Let me tell you a little something about cults.

23:34.000 --> 23:35.700
What's going on?

23:37.000 --> 23:38.700
You letting me go?

23:44.800 --> 23:46.700
Hello. Richard.

24:28.700 --> 24:31.000
What's with the dopey grin?

24:31.800 --> 24:34.400
Nothing. Just the way that you...

24:34.500 --> 24:37.500
you bite on your tongue when you're trying to concentrate.

24:38.200 --> 24:40.100
I've been doing that since I was a kid.

24:40.200 --> 24:42.500
How long have you been in seattle?

24:44.000 --> 24:45.700
Two years.

24:46.700 --> 24:49.100
Left my mom and her new boyfriend

24:49.200 --> 24:51.700
and came out here for the music.

24:52.000 --> 24:54.700
Somehow. My life took a weird turn.

24:55.500 --> 24:57.900
I've had a few of those myself.

24:58.100 --> 25:00.400
What. You run away from home too?

25:00.500 --> 25:02.100
Um...

25:02.200 --> 25:03.800
sort of.

25:04.000 --> 25:07.300
Except I lucked out. I found a place to run to.

25:07.400 --> 25:08.000
Otherwise...

25:08.100 --> 25:11.200
you would have wound up like the rest of us rejects?

25:11.800 --> 25:14.000
Something like that.

25:16.500 --> 25:19.600
You're one of those 4400 guys. Huh?

25:20.800 --> 25:23.100
Can you make my eyes turn green?

25:23.300 --> 25:25.600
What. You able to walk on water?

25:25.700 --> 25:28.700
I like your eyes the way that they are.

25:28.800 --> 25:30.900
And I can barely swim.

25:48.800 --> 25:49.900
Come on. Now.

25:50.000 --> 25:52.800
What the hell is this?

25:53.300 --> 25:54.800
Dewey...

25:57.000 --> 25:58.300
I see you been keeping busy.

25:58.400 --> 25:58.900
No. Baby.

25:58.901 --> 26:00.500
He's just some guy...

26:00.600 --> 26:02.400
bought us some food and blankets.

26:02.500 --> 26:03.800
Liv. Who is this guy?

26:03.900 --> 26:06.000
Shawn. You got to go.

26:06.700 --> 26:08.700
I'd listen to her.

26:09.100 --> 26:09.800
What are you doing?

26:09.900 --> 26:13.000
Well. See. She does whatever I tell her to do.

26:13.400 --> 26:15.400
Do you have a problem with that?

26:15.900 --> 26:16.800
Yeah.

26:16.900 --> 26:17.600
Yeah. I do.

26:17.700 --> 26:18.700
Shawn. Please.

26:18.800 --> 26:20.800
You've done your good deed. Just...

26:20.900 --> 26:23.400
just go home. Okay? Please.

26:23.500 --> 26:25.400
Come with me.

26:25.900 --> 26:27.600
Come with me.

26:29.200 --> 26:30.700
And then what?

26:30.800 --> 26:33.100
What. You gonna rescue me?

26:33.600 --> 26:35.800
I don't want to be saved.

26:36.100 --> 26:38.000
Get the hell out of here.

26:39.000 --> 26:40.900
Go. I mean it.

26:42.300 --> 26:43.800
Go!

26:58.100 --> 26:59.300
Hey.

26:59.400 --> 27:01.100
You're not going back to that school.

27:01.200 --> 27:02.700
Not till that woman is gone.

27:02.800 --> 27:04.600
But what about my other classes?

27:04.700 --> 27:06.000
I've got homework.

27:06.100 --> 27:07.700
Since when do you care about school?

27:07.800 --> 27:09.000
You want me to wind up like you?

27:09.001 --> 27:10.100
Hey. You watch your mouth.

27:10.300 --> 27:11.800
I don't want to fall behind.

27:11.900 --> 27:13.200
"Fall behind"?

27:13.300 --> 27:15.000
With the grades you've been bringing home?

27:15.100 --> 27:17.700
You been behind since your first report card.

27:22.700 --> 27:23.300
What. You just going to sit there.

27:23.400 --> 27:24.700
Or are you going to talk to me?

27:24.800 --> 27:27.400
'Cause I really think you owe me an explanation.

27:27.500 --> 27:29.000
You know. Those guys wanted to kill me.

27:29.100 --> 27:30.200
And I turn around.

27:30.300 --> 27:31.500
And my cousin's nowhere in sight.

27:31.600 --> 27:32.600
I don't know what happened.

27:32.601 --> 27:35.000
Yeah. I know what happened... you ran out on me.

27:35.100 --> 27:36.600
It's a good thing that security guard was there.

27:36.700 --> 27:38.000
The other time. I could blame it on the beer.

27:38.100 --> 27:38.900
You drink too much.

27:38.901 --> 27:39.700
You can black out. Right?

27:39.800 --> 27:43.300
But today. I didn't drink anything.

27:44.000 --> 27:46.000
I'm blacking out.

27:47.500 --> 27:49.800
Iosing chunks of time.

27:51.300 --> 27:53.000
It's like they did something to my wiring.

27:53.100 --> 27:54.600
They?

27:55.600 --> 27:57.100
Kyle. Who are you talking about?

27:57.200 --> 27:59.000
The same ones who took shawn.

27:59.100 --> 28:01.100
Who put me in the coma.

28:03.100 --> 28:05.600
They left me messed up inside.

28:05.700 --> 28:07.300
Hey. Man. You're scaring me.

28:07.400 --> 28:09.600
How do you think I feel?

28:12.700 --> 28:13.800
Brian.

28:13.900 --> 28:14.600
Any news?

28:14.700 --> 28:16.200
Yeah. I got ahold of the weldon authorities.

28:16.300 --> 28:18.300
And richard's been released from custody.

28:18.400 --> 28:19.500
Oh. Thank god.

28:19.600 --> 28:20.900
When?

28:21.000 --> 28:23.200
About an hour ago.

28:23.300 --> 28:25.500
Why hasn't he called?

28:36.600 --> 28:38.400
You sure you don't want to call lily.

28:38.500 --> 28:40.700
Let her know you're all right?

28:40.900 --> 28:41.800
Am I?

28:41.900 --> 28:43.700
You're in no danger from me. Richard.

28:43.800 --> 28:46.000
All I want is to make you an offer.

28:46.100 --> 28:47.000
If it's not to your liking.

28:47.100 --> 28:48.300
You can walk out of here.

28:48.400 --> 28:50.100
You'll never see me again.

28:50.200 --> 28:54.300
How much did you pay those cops to call you 
instead of ntac to get my picture into their hands?

28:54.301 --> 28:56.800
It's my money. Richard.

28:57.100 --> 28:58.800
Look.

28:59.100 --> 29:02.500
You said I was free to go after I heard your offer.

29:02.800 --> 29:03.800
If you got one for me.

29:03.900 --> 29:05.200
Make it.

29:05.300 --> 29:07.200
I want you to come home.

29:07.300 --> 29:08.700
You and your family.

29:08.800 --> 29:11.400
To the 4400 center.

29:11.700 --> 29:12.600
I don't think so.

29:12.700 --> 29:14.500
You said you read my book.

29:14.600 --> 29:17.800
Which means you know why we were 
taken and what we're meant to do.

29:17.900 --> 29:19.700
The future...

29:19.800 --> 29:22.400
The future rests in our hands. Richard.

29:22.500 --> 29:24.700
You. Me. Lily... we are the chosen ones.

29:24.800 --> 29:26.700
Come on. Jordan.

29:27.400 --> 29:30.400
We both know this has nothing to do with me or lily.

29:30.500 --> 29:33.000
This is all about isabelle.

29:33.100 --> 29:34.700
Isabelle.

29:34.800 --> 29:36.000
Well. That's a lovely name.

29:36.100 --> 29:37.000
For once.

29:37.100 --> 29:39.100
Why don't you say what you really want...

29:39.200 --> 29:40.900
to take her from us. Control her.

29:41.000 --> 29:45.000
Your daughter is the future.

29:45.100 --> 29:46.700
I believed that then. I believe it now.

29:46.800 --> 29:47.800
Then what's changed?

29:47.900 --> 29:50.000
I have.

29:55.400 --> 29:56.600
I'll need more than your word.

29:56.700 --> 29:58.200
Of course.

29:58.300 --> 29:59.300
Bring me to isabelle.

29:59.400 --> 30:00.200
Let her judge me.

30:00.300 --> 30:01.500
Isabelle's not coming anywhere near you.

30:01.600 --> 30:03.000
What are you afraid of. Richard?

30:03.100 --> 30:04.600
I'm the one at risk.

30:04.700 --> 30:07.400
I'm still suffering the after-effects of our last encounter.

30:07.500 --> 30:09.700
Richard. It's simple.

30:09.800 --> 30:11.400
If I'm lying.

30:11.500 --> 30:13.300
If my motives are not pure.

30:13.400 --> 30:15.900
Isabelle will punish me accordingly.

30:16.000 --> 30:19.100
And you'll be free of me once and for all.

30:20.000 --> 30:22.200
But if I'm sincere.

30:22.400 --> 30:24.700
If isabelle accepts me.

30:25.400 --> 30:30.000
Well. Then. I can offer you and lily and the child a new life.

30:30.100 --> 30:33.600
Stop running. Richard.

30:59.200 --> 31:00.200
Forget it.

31:00.300 --> 31:02.100
It's not going to happen.

31:02.200 --> 31:05.000
There's no way I'm going to allow isabelle 
anywhere near that man.

31:05.100 --> 31:06.800
But think about it.

31:06.900 --> 31:09.100
If collier really has changed.

31:09.200 --> 31:11.600
It means we can get off the road. Stop running.

31:11.700 --> 31:13.400
That's a big if.

31:13.500 --> 31:16.000
He offered to act as a middleman between us and ntac.

31:16.100 --> 31:17.100
Says he can get them to back off.

31:17.200 --> 31:19.100
And you believe him?

31:19.200 --> 31:20.200
He's got lawyers.

31:20.300 --> 31:22.700
A whole organization behind him.

31:22.800 --> 31:23.900
We can barely even pay for gas.

31:24.000 --> 31:25.700
He's lied to us before.

31:25.800 --> 31:28.200
The man tried to destroy our relationship.

31:28.300 --> 31:30.500
Okay. Let's say he is lying.

31:30.600 --> 31:32.000
Maybe all of this is some kind of trap...

31:32.001 --> 31:33.600
to get his hands on our daughter.

31:33.700 --> 31:35.000
He wants a face-to-face with isabelle?

31:35.100 --> 31:36.700
I say we give it to him.

31:36.800 --> 31:38.200
You've seen what she's capable of.

31:38.300 --> 31:40.200
What she can do if she feels threatened.

31:40.300 --> 31:42.300
It still feels like an awful big risk.

31:42.301 --> 31:44.100
For collier.

31:49.300 --> 31:52.000
Stand back. Let her through.

32:02.400 --> 32:04.300
Get out of here!

32:06.000 --> 32:07.300
Welcome back. Heather.

32:07.400 --> 32:08.900
I'm sorry about all of this.

32:09.000 --> 32:10.700
Once the media loses interest.

32:10.701 --> 32:11.900
Things will die down.

32:12.000 --> 32:12.600
Until it does.

32:12.601 --> 32:14.900
We need to discuss how you intend to handle security.

32:15.000 --> 32:16.000
Let me get heather situated.

32:16.100 --> 32:17.600
Then I'll meet you in my office.

32:17.601 --> 32:21.100
- Come on.
- Don't get comfortable. Freak! You're not staying!

32:33.700 --> 32:37.000
I like this one with the smoke and the clouds...

32:37.500 --> 32:39.100
Greg.

32:39.400 --> 32:42.100
Does your father know you're here?

32:43.000 --> 32:45.100
It's all your fault.

32:45.200 --> 32:48.100
Everything was okay till you showed up.

32:48.600 --> 32:49.500
Greg.

32:49.600 --> 32:51.000
Please put the gun down.

32:51.100 --> 32:52.400
No.

32:52.700 --> 32:53.800
You made me do this.

32:53.900 --> 32:55.800
I have no choice.

32:55.900 --> 32:57.200
Yes. You do.

32:57.300 --> 32:58.400
But only if you put the gun away.

32:58.500 --> 33:00.900
I can't be here anymore. My dad won't let me.

33:00.901 --> 33:02.400
This is my last chance.

33:02.401 --> 33:03.500
Greg. Calm down...

33:03.600 --> 33:04.900
no!

33:05.000 --> 33:08.800
Not until you change me like you did them.

33:08.900 --> 33:10.700
You have to!

33:15.700 --> 33:17.700
There's nothing to discuss.

33:17.800 --> 33:19.400
I'll take anything.

33:19.500 --> 33:20.400
Violin.

33:20.500 --> 33:21.200
Painting.

33:21.300 --> 33:22.600
Photography. I don't care!

33:22.700 --> 33:24.600
Listen. Greg.

33:24.700 --> 33:26.500
You're problem is with me.

33:26.600 --> 33:28.500
Not your classmates.

33:28.600 --> 33:29.700
Let them go.

33:29.800 --> 33:33.900
And you and i will deal with this alone.

33:35.800 --> 33:37.400
Yeah. Sure.

33:37.800 --> 33:39.600
That works for me.

33:41.000 --> 33:42.400
Okay.

33:42.500 --> 33:44.700
I'd like you all to leave now.

33:44.800 --> 33:46.200
Quietly. Don't run.

33:46.201 --> 33:47.600
Ms. Tobey. Will you be okay?

33:47.700 --> 33:49.100
Move!

33:49.900 --> 33:50.700
Go on.

33:59.300 --> 34:00.800
For an entire week?

34:00.900 --> 34:02.100
Is that really necessary?

34:02.200 --> 34:04.100
To and from school. Strictly as a precaution.

34:04.200 --> 34:08.330
- A continued police presence will send a
clear message to anyone who feels they can...
- Okay.

34:10.000 --> 34:11.100
So now we're alone.

34:11.199 --> 34:12.400
Now. Do whatyou promised!

34:12.500 --> 34:13.500
Would you put the gun down.

34:13.600 --> 34:15.300
- No!
- Greg?

34:15.400 --> 34:16.600
Please. Put the gun down.

34:16.699 --> 34:18.000
It scares me.

34:18.100 --> 34:18.500
Well. Good.

34:18.501 --> 34:19.699
It's supposed to scare you!

34:19.701 --> 34:20.500
Greg...

34:20.600 --> 34:22.199
D.A. Says we don't have a criminal case.

34:22.300 --> 34:23.699
Fine. We'll take it to civil court.

34:23.800 --> 34:25.400
- One way or another...
- excuse us.

34:25.500 --> 34:26.600
Hey. Buddy. What's your problem?

34:26.699 --> 34:28.500
You're needed inside.

34:34.900 --> 34:36.100
I don't feel any different.

34:36.199 --> 34:37.199
Greg. I'm trying.

34:37.300 --> 34:39.000
Well. Try harder.

34:39.100 --> 34:40.800
You found it in mike. In rita...

34:40.900 --> 34:42.500
you can find it in me!

34:42.600 --> 34:43.400
I told you.

34:43.500 --> 34:44.800
I told you she was dangerous.

34:44.900 --> 34:45.600
None of you would listen.

34:45.699 --> 34:47.000
She's not the one holding the gun.

34:47.001 --> 34:48.800
Greg is a kid.

34:48.900 --> 34:50.600
He doesn't know what he's doing.

34:50.699 --> 34:52.699
She's got his mind all twisted.

34:52.800 --> 34:53.900
I got news for you.

34:54.000 --> 34:56.400
I knew everything I needed to know the first time I talked to greg.

34:56.500 --> 34:57.400
You're the one who twisted his mind.

34:57.500 --> 34:59.500
- You put that gun in his hand.
- That is not true.

34:59.600 --> 35:01.700
We both know it's true...

35:03.300 --> 35:06.700
and now you're the only one who's going to get your son out of this alive.

35:08.900 --> 35:10.300
